      <hedline>
        <hl1>Wash Your Hands (Don't Forget the Soap)</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ann Haeussler letter says number of people who do not wash their hands after using toilet may be even higher than reported if one includes those people who merely run their hands under water (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Washing Up Is Down, Study Shows'' (news article, Sept. 19):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Washing Up Is Down, Study Shows'' (news article, Sept. 19):</p>
        <p>I am amazed at how few people wash their hands after using the bathroom. But I am a bit unclear about one thing: Are people who don't use soap considered to be among the ''washers'' or the ''nonwashers''?</p>
        <p>Clearly, running your hands under the water is no substitute for good old soap and elbow grease. Yet many people consider wetting their hands to be enough. With that in mind, the number of ''nonwashers'' may be even higher than reported! Not a comforting thought, I'm afraid.</p>
        <p>ANN HAEUSSLER  Union, N.J., Sept. 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
